    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Door Switch and Flasher Light Modules</title>
        <para>The switch modules in the steering wheel assembly are easily removed. The left hand switch module controls
            the opening and closing of the side passenger entry door. The right side switch module controls the amber
            flasher and red override switch.
        </para>
        <figure id="f47006224" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G47006224.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 224. Steering Wheel Switch Modules Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. MODULE DIRECTION FOR REMOVAL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the switch modules from the steering wheel, slide them toward the center (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006224">Figure 224</hotlnk>) of the steering wheel assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
